title: For Sale:  Blueprinted LH Remington 700 280 Ackley Improved
postcontent:
Attention left hand shooters... For your consideration is a blueprinted LEFT HANDED Remington 700 chambered in 280 Ackley Improved. The LH action has been squared and trued center to bore; the inner tenon was opened up .010" and new threads were single point cut center to bore. The actions lugs have also been squared and trued. The bolt lugs, as well as the bolt nose and face have been trued and squared. All machine work is done on a precision lathe with a single point cuter all center to bore. Both the action and bolt are dial indicated to .0001" before any work is performed.

 A brand new Shilen, match grade, chrome barrel was used for this custom build. The contour is a #4 (classic sporter contour), 9 twist and finished at 24". The barrel threads were also single point cut and hand fit to this action. The breech was cut to .0035" and the headspace was cut to .0015". This is much tighter than factory specs and will lead to a much more accurate shooter. The barrel was crowned with an 11 degree target crown.  I have plenty of pics to share showing the machine work being completed.

 Once the machine work was completed and the rifle test fired the barreled action was caustic blued but can always be customized to your needs... Maybe add a muzzle brake; cerakote finish; detachable mag; Jewell trigger; custom paint the stock; ect.

 The barreled action in a quality stock will easily shoot 3/4 MOA with factory ammo and is capable of 1/2 MOA or better using hand loaded ammo. I have a few HS precision stocks and a few Bell and Carlson stocks to offer with this build.  Willing to sell just the barreled action for 1300 if you already have a stock and bottom metal.  The barreled action will include the firing pin assembly and factory left handed trigger - I know they are not in the pics but will be included in the barreled action price.  Send a note for more detailed pics.

 I have a few other blueprinted Rem 700s available as well so if you have another caliber in mind send a note... I probably have it or can build it.

 Will ship to your FFL if needed.

ART IV Scope Background: 
. The A.R.T. IV is a superior quality variable power telescopic sighting system commercially manufactured by Buris and sold by Springfield Armory in the mid to late 1980s.

How to Use: 
. Zero the rifle at 200 yards. 
. The two stadia lines at the bottom represent 18 inches at any distance. 
. Dial magnification until 18 inches of target fits into the two stadia lines. 
. The center horizontal crosshair splits and begins to separate. If shooting at 200 yards (at any magnification between 3x and 9x), use the top crosshair. title: For Sale/Trade:  WW2 Japanese Type I Arisaka
postcontent:
WW2 Japanese Type I Arisaka rifle.  Chambered in the original 6.5mm JAP.  In great condition with cleaning rod.  These are unique rifles that the Japanese Imperial Navy had manufactured under contract by the Italian gun maker solely for use by the Navy.  While the Imperial Army had their Type 38's, 44's, and 99's, the Navy had the Type I.
The Type I uses the same 6.5mm JAP round that the Type 38 rifles used, and is built with many similarities to the Type 38 long rifle, except that it never had a "mum" stamped them and that these rifles were outfitted with a "carcano" type bolt action.
A great piece of WW2 history in great condition.  NO import marks.

$300 Cash Firm, or equivalent value in trade.   I strongly prefer to deal with individuals that are also OH Concealed Handgun License holders or fellow NRA Instructors.  

Additional pics upon request.
